<div class="page" id="page-travel">
  <div class="page-inner" style="max-width:760px;">
    <p class="section-label">Getting There</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Travel &amp; Logistics</h2>
    <div class="section-divider"></div>

    <div class="travel-section">
      <h3 class="travel-heading">&#9992; Flying to Italy</h3>
      <p class="travel-text">Most guests will fly internationally into <strong>Rome Fiumicino (FCO)</strong>, which is the largest and most well-connected airport — about 2.5–3 hours from Petritoli by car.</p>
      <p class="travel-text">If you're already traveling in Europe or plan to visit Rome before the wedding, you can also fly into one of these regional airports closer to Petritoli:</p>
      <div class="travel-detail-list">
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">Ancona Falconara (AOI)</span><span class="travel-detail-info">~1 hr drive</span></div>
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">Pescara (PSR)</span><span class="travel-detail-info">~1.5 hr drive</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="travel-section">
      <h3 class="travel-heading">&#128646; By Train</h3>
      <p class="travel-text">Italy's train network is excellent and scenic. If you're already in the country, these are the nearest stations to Petritoli:</p>
      <div class="travel-detail-list">
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">Pedaso</span><span class="travel-detail-info">Regional · 15 min drive</span></div>
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">Porto San Giorgio</span><span class="travel-detail-info">Intercity · 30 min drive</span></div>
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">Ancona</span><span class="travel-detail-info">Fast trains · 1 hr drive</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="travel-section">
      <h3 class="travel-heading">&#128663; Getting to Petritoli</h3>
      <p class="travel-text">Once you've landed or arrived by train, you have two options to reach us:</p>
      <p class="travel-text"><strong>Rent a car</strong> — great if you want flexibility to explore the region on your own before or after the wedding.</p>
      <p class="travel-text"><strong>Shuttle</strong> — we're happy to help arrange group shuttles from airports and train stations. Just indicate on your <a href="#" onclick="showPage('rsvp');return false;" style="color:var(--fresh-orange);text-decoration:underline;">RSVP</a> that you'd like shuttle coordination and share your arrival details — we'll group guests by timing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="travel-section">
      <h3 class="travel-heading">&#127969; Once You're in Petritoli</h3>
      <p class="travel-text">You won't need a car for the week! All events will either be in town or at the Palazzo, and we'll organize transportation for anything off-site (like the beach day). Sit back, relax, and let us handle the logistics.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="travel-section">
      <h3 class="travel-heading">&#128203; Before You Go Checklist</h3>
      <p class="travel-text">A few important things to sort out before you book your flights:</p>
      <div class="travel-detail-list">
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">&#128188; Passport</span><span class="travel-detail-info">Must be valid 6+ months beyond travel dates</span></div>
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">&#127758; Visa</span><span class="travel-detail-info">U.S./Canadian citizens — no visa needed. Others — check Schengen requirements</span></div>
        <div class="travel-detail-item"><span class="travel-detail-name">&#128663; International Driving Permit</span><span class="travel-detail-info">Required if you plan to rent a car in Italy</span></div>
      </div>
      <p class="travel-text" style="margin-top:18px;">Need an invitation letter for your visa application? Just let us know — we're happy to provide one.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
